Kitsanas-MacBook-Pro:~ Kitsana.Dounglomchan$ curl http://localhost:6270/v1/prices/names/kitsana.id
{"name_price": {"satoshis": 2500, "btc": 2.5e-05}, "total_tx_fees": 102440, "register_tx_fee": {"satoshis": 50380, "btc": 0.0005038}, "preorder_tx_fee": {"satoshis": 52060, "btc": 0.0005206}, "warnings": ["Insufficient funds (need 104940, have 0).  Fees are rough estimates."], "total_estimated_cost": {"satoshis": 104940, "btc": 0.0010494}}

**Error**

Kitsanas-MacBook-Pro:~ Kitsana.Dounglomchan$ curl http://localhost:6270/v1/prices/names/kit.personal.id {"error": "Not a valid name: \n * The name is invalid"}

By default validation errors will be formatted like so:
``` js
{
    errors: [{
        detail: 'First name is required',
        source: {
            pointer: '/data/attributes/first-name'
        },
        status: '400'
    }]
}
```

However if you want to throw a custom validation error you can pass a dictionary and it will be used:
``` python
def validate_first_name(self, data):
    raise ValidationError({ 'detail': 'Gimme your first name' })
```
results in
``` js
{
    errors: [{
        detail: 'First name is required'
    }]
}
```

